der Swadesh Darshan Scheme. The second installment for spiritual tourism circuits development can only be sanctioned after receiving the details of utilization of 1st installment amount."}, "004-section": {"000-title": "Target of 40 Million Tourists by 2026", "001-normal": "The central govt. has set a target of around 40 million tourists annually across the country by FY 2026. Union govt. aims to develop Kerala as a must visit destination as the current ranking of the state in terms of domestic tourists arrivals is 16th and 8th in foreign tourists arrivals. The neighboring Tamil Nadu state currently holds 1st and 3rd spot respectively.", "002-normal": "Central govt. is providing wide publicity for Kerala to get over the post flood crisis. From then onward, there is shortage of around 18.5% in tourist arrivals to the state. Many people outside the state has an opinion that tourism destinations in Kerala are yet to recover from the havoc caused by the deluge. Tourism ministry is working hard to convince tourists that Kerala\u2019s tourism sector is back on track."}}